Pre-Game Insights: Ireland’s focus has been on the shorter forms of the game, and while they have six T20 wins from 14 games, three of those were against non-Test playing countries.
Paul Stirling and Harry Tector have struggled with form, with Stirling managing just one half-century and Tector going 11 innings without reaching 20.
Josh Little’s rare availability and Barry McCarthy’s injury haven’t helped the seam attack.
